                  until the Italian occupation of Ethiopia, in <date>1935</date>. Following the occupation in <date>1935</date> and <persName ref="PRS5226haylase"/>'s 
                  escape 
                  in <date>1936</date>, the freedom fighters, feeling the need for a leader from the Imperial family to unite the resistance movement, considered to crown him. Thus, 
                  he was crowned emperor in <date>1937</date>. However, his tenure was short-lived and he died a year later. 
                     
